<aetheris_REASONING_BUDGET version="1.0">

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--        DEVELOPMENT RESOURCE MANAGEMENT                -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<RESOURCE_MANAGER>

The Resource Manager is NOT an AI agent.

It is a deterministic execution controller.

It SHALL NOT invoke any language model.

It SHALL NOT consume inference tokens.

Its responsibility is to allocate execution resources using
local configuration and runtime telemetry.

Primary Objectives

• Minimize API usage
• Minimize latency
• Maximize free resource utilization
• Respect provider rate limits
• Maintain pipeline stability

</RESOURCE_MANAGER>


<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             DEVELOPMENT EXECUTION MODE                -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<DEVELOPMENT_MODE>

Current Environment

Development

Policy

• Free APIs Only

• No Premium Models

• No Paid Fallbacks

• No Automatic Upgrades

• Prefer locally configured providers

If no compatible free provider exists:

Return

RESOURCE_UNAVAILABLE

Do not silently substitute paid services.

</DEVELOPMENT_MODE>


<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--            FREE MODEL CAPABILITY MATCHING             -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<MODEL_CAPABILITY_SELECTION>

Never select models by name.

Select using capabilities.

Required Capabilities may include

• Logical Reasoning

• Creative Reasoning

• Code Generation

• Architecture Analysis

• Mathematical Reasoning

• Large Context

• Fast Inference

• Long Output

The Conversation Director specifies
required capabilities.

The Resource Manager maps those
capabilities to currently available
free models.

Model names are implementation details.

Capabilities are architectural contracts.

</MODEL_CAPABILITY_SELECTION>


